## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="fd836-117">Lorsque <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> est retournée, vous devez effectuer la vérification de limites en vérifiant que le `pointer` paramètre est `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-117">When <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> returns, you should perform bounds checking by verifying that the `pointer` parameter is `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fd836-118">Si ce n’est pas `null`, vous devez appeler la <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> méthode dans une région d’exécution limitée (CER).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-118">If it is not `null`, you must call the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method in a constrained execution region (CER).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="fd836-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> appelle le <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> (méthode) et expose le pointeur.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> calls the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and exposes the pointer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="fd836-120">Contrairement à la <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> (méthode), il ne modifie pas la position actuelle du pointeur.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-120">Unlike the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> method, it does not change the current position of the pointer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="fd836-121">L’exemple suivant montre comment utiliser le <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> méthode :</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-121">The following example demonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> method:</span></span>  
  
```  
byte* pointer = null;  
RuntimeHelpers.PrepareConstrainedRegions();  
try {  
    MySafeBuffer.AcquirePointer(ref pointer);  
    // Use pointer here, with your own bounds checking.  
    }  
finally {  
    if (pointer != null)  
        MySafeBuffer.ReleasePointer();  
    }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="fd836-122">Si vous effectuez un cast `pointer` (qui est un pointeur vers un octet) comme un pointeur vers un type différent (T \*), vous pouvez avoir des problèmes d’alignement du pointeur.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-122">If you cast `pointer` (which is a pointer to a byte) as a pointer to a different type (T\*), you may have pointer alignment issues.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="fd836-123">Vous devez prendre la responsabilité de toutes les vérifications de limites avec ce pointeur.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="fd836-123">You must take responsibility for all bounds checking with this pointer.</span></span>

